Health minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize, is giving an update on Covid-19 cases in SA. SA has recorded its first three deaths attributed to Covid-19 while the number of confirmed cases has risen over 1,326 by Monday. In the public interest none of our coronavirus news coverage will be behind our paywall, it is available free for all to read. If you would like to support our mission of delivering award-winning, independent local news, please consider taking out a subscription by clicking here: www.dispatchLIVE.co.za/buy/.